rong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerfulINSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("374", "Beldum", "Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout BELDUM’s body. This POKéMON communicates withINSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("375", "Metang", "When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are joined by a magnetic nervous system.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("376", "Metagross", "METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations fasterINSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("377", "Regirock", "REGIROCK was sealed away by people long ago. If this POKéMON’s body is damaged in battle, it is said to seekINSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("378", "Regice", "REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("379", "Registeel", "REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("380", "Latias", "LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKéMON ruffles theINSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("381", "Latios", "LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("382", "Kyogre", "KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("383", "Groudon", "GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("384", "Rayquaza", "RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer,  never descending to the ground.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("385", "Jirachi", "A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("386", "Deoxys-normal", "The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS.INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("387", "Turtwig", "Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("388", "Grotle", "It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("389", "Torterra", "Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("390", "Chimchar", "It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("391", "Monferno", "To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("392", "Infernape", "It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("393", "Piplup", "Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("394", "Prinplup", "It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("395", "Empoleon", "The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("396", "Starly", "They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("397", "Staravia", "It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("398", "Staraptor", "It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("399", "Bidoof", "With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("400", "Bibarel", "It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("401", "Kricketot", "It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("402", "Kricketune", "It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("403", "Shinx", "All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("404", "Luxio", "Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("405", "Luxray", "It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("406", "Budew", "Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("407", "Roserade", "It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("408", "Cranidos", "It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("409", "Rampardos", "Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("410", "Shieldon", "A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("411", "Bastiodon", "Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("412", "Burmy", "To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("413", "Wormadam-plant", "When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("414", "Mothim", "It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("415", "Combee", "A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("416", "Vespiquen", "Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("417", "Pachirisu", "It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("418", "Buizel", "It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("419", "Floatzel", "It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("420", "Cherubi", "The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("421", "Cherrim", "It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("422", "Shellos", "Its colors and shapes differ from region to region. In the Sinnoh region, two types are confirmed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("423", "Gastrodon", "It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("424", "Ambipom", "To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("425", "Drifloon", "A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("426", "Drifblim", "It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("427", "Buneary", "It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("428", "Lopunny", "An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("429", "Mismagius", "Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("430", "Honchkrow", "Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("431", "Glameow", "It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("432", "Purugly", "It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("433", "Chingling", "It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("434", "Stunky", "It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("435", "Skuntank", "It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("436", "Bronzor", "Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("437", "Bronzong", "One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("438", "Bonsly", "It looks as if it is always crying. It is actually adjusting its body’s fluid levels by eliminating excess.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("439", "Mime-jr", "It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("440", "Happiny", "It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("441", "Chatot", "It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("442", "Spiritomb", "A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("443", "Gible", "It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("444", "Gabite", "There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("445", "Garchomp", "When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("446", "Munchlax", "It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("447", "Riolu", "The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("448", "Lucario", "It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("449", "Hippopotas", "It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("450", "Hippowdon", "It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("451", "Skorupi", "It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("452", "Drapion", "It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("453", "Croagunk", "Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("454", "Toxicroak", "Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("455", "Carnivine", "It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("456", "Finneon", "After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("457", "Lumineon", "It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("458", "Mantyke", "A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("459", "Snover", "It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("460", "Abomasnow", "It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("461", "Weavile", "They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("462", "Magnezone", "It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("463", "Lickilicky", "It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("464", "Rhyperior", "It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("465", "Tangrowth", "It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("466", "Electivire", "It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("467", "Magmortar", "It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("468", "Togekiss", "It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("469", "Yanmega", "By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("470", "Leafeon", "Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("471", "Glaceon", "As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("472", "Gliscor", "It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("473", "Mamoswine", "Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("474", "Porygon-z", "Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("475", "Gallade", "A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("476", "Probopass", "It exudes strong magnetism from all over. It controls three small units called Mini-Noses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("477", "Dusknoir", "The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("478", "Froslass", "It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("479", "Rotom", "Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("480", "Uxie", "Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("481", "Mesprit", "Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("482", "Azelf", "Known as “The Being of Willpower.” It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("483", "Dialga", "It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("484", "Palkia", "It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("485", "Heatran", "It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("486", "Regigigas", "There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("487", "Giratina-altered", "A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("488", "Cresselia", "Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("489", "Phione", "A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("490", "Manaphy", "Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("491", "Darkrai", "It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("492", "Shaymin-land", "It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("493", "Arceus", "It is described in mythology as the Pokémon that shaped the universe with its 1,000 arms.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("494", "Victini", "This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("495", "Snivy", "It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("496", "Servine", "It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("497", "Serperior", "It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("498", "Tepig", "It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("499", "Pignite", "When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("500", "Emboar", "It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("501", "Oshawott", "It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("502", "Dewott", "Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("503", "Samurott", "One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("504", "Patrat", "Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("505", "Watchog", "When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("506", "Lillipup", "It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("507", "Herdier", "It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("508", "Stoutland", "It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("509", "Purrloin", "They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("510", "Liepard", "These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("511", "Pansage", "This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("512", "Simisage", "Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("513", "Pansear", "When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("514", "Simisear", "It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("515", "Panpour", "The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("516", "Simipour", "The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("517", "Munna", "Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("518", "Musharna", "The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("519", "Pidove", "Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("520", "Tranquill", "It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("521", "Unfezant", "Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("522", "Blitzle", "Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("523", "Zebstrika", "They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("524", "Roggenrola", "Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("525", "Boldore", "When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("526", "Gigalith", "Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("527", "Woobat", "Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("528", "Swoobat", "It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("529", "Drilbur", "It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("530", "Excadrill", "It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("531", "Audino", "It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("532", "Timburr", "It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("533", "Gurdurr", "This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("534", "Conkeldurr", "It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("535", "Tympole", "They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("536", "Palpitoad", "When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("537", "Seismitoad", "They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("538", "Throh", "When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("539", "Sawk", "The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("540", "Sewaddle", "Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("541", "Swadloon", "Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("542", "Leavanny", "Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("543", "Venipede", "Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("544", "Whirlipede", "Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("545", "Scolipede", "With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("546", "Cottonee", "When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("547", "Whimsicott", "Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("548", "Petilil", "The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("549", "Lilligant", "Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("550", "Basculin-red-striped", "Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("551", "Sandile", "They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("552", "Krokorok", "They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("553", "Krookodile", "They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("554", "Darumaka", "When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("555", "Darmanitan-standard", "Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("556", "Maractus", "It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("557", "Dwebble", "This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("558", "Crustle", "Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("559", "Scraggy", "Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("560", "Scrafty", "Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("561", "Sigilyph", "They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("562", "Yamask", "Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("563", "Cofagrigus", "It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("564", "Tirtouga", "Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("565", "Carracosta", "They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("566", "Archen", "Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("567", "Archeops", "They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("568", "Trubbish", "Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("569", "Garbodor", "It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("570", "Zorua", "It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("571", "Zoroark", "Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("572", "Minccino", "They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("573", "Cinccino", "Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("574", "Gothita", "Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("575", "Gothorita", "They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("576", "Gothitelle", "Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("577", "Solosis", "They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("578", "Duosion", "Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("579", "Reuniclus", "When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("580", "Ducklett", "These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("581", "Swanna", "Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("582", "Vanillite", "The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("583", "Vanillish", "Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("584", "Vanilluxe", "Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("585", "Deerling", "The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("586", "Sawsbuck", "They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("587", "Emolga", "The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("588", "Karrablast", "These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("589", "Escavalier", "They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("590", "Foongus", "It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("591", "Amoonguss", "It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("592", "Frillish", "With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("593", "Jellicent", "The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("594", "Alomomola", "The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("595", "Joltik", "Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("596", "Galvantula", "When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("597", "Ferroseed", "When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("598", "Ferrothorn", "It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("599", "Klink", "The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("600", "Klang", "By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("601", "Klinklang", "Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("602", "Tynamo", "While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("603", "Eelektrik", "They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("604", "Eelektross", "They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("605", "Elgyem", "It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("606", "Beheeyem", "It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("607", "Litwick", "Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("608", "Lampent", "This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("609", "Chandelure", "It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("610", "Axew", "They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("611", "Fraxure", "Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("612", "Haxorus", "They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("613", "Cubchoo", "When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("614", "Beartic", "It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("615", "Cryogonal", "When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("616", "Shelmet", "When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("617", "Accelgor", "When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("618", "Stunfisk", "Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("619", "Mienfoo", "In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("620", "Mienshao", "It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("621", "Druddigon", "It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("622", "Golett", "The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("623", "Golurk", "It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("624", "Pawniard", "Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("625", "Bisharp", "It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("626", "Bouffalant", "Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("627", "Rufflet", "They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("628", "Braviary", "They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("629", "Vullaby", "Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("630", "Mandibuzz", "It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("631", "Heatmor", "It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("632", "Durant", "They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("633", "Deino", "It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("634", "Zweilous", "After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("635", "Hydreigon", "This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("636", "Larvesta", "This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("637", "Volcarona", "When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("638", "Cobalion", "This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("639", "Terrakion", "This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("640", "Virizion", "This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("641", "Tornadus-incarnate", "The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("642", "Thundurus-incarnate", "Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("643", "Reshiram", "This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("644", "Zekrom", "Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("645", "Landorus-incarnate", "Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("646", "Kyurem", "It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("647", "Keldeo-ordinary", "By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("648", "Meloetta-aria", "Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("649", "Genesect", "Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("650", "Chespin", "The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("651", "Quilladin", "It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predators’ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("652", "Chesnaught", "Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("653", "Fennekin", "Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("654", "Braixen", "It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("655", "Delphox", "It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("656", "Froakie", "It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("657", "Frogadier", "It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("658", "Greninja", "It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("659", "Bunnelby", "They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("660", "Diggersby", "With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("661", "Fletchling", "These friendly Pokémon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("662", "Fletchinder", "From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("663", "Talonflame", "In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("664", "Scatterbug", "When under attack from bird Pokémon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("665", "Spewpa", "It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("666", "Vivillon", "Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("667", "Litleo", "The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("668", "Pyroar", "The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("669", "Flabebe", "It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower Flabébé holds is most likely part of its body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("670", "Floette", "It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("671", "Florges", "It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("672", "Skiddo", "Thought to be one of the first Pokémon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("673", "Gogoat", "It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("674", "Pancham", "It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("675", "Pangoro", "Although it possesses a violent temperament, it won’t put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("676", "Furfrou", "Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("677", "Espurr", "The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("678", "Meowstic-male", "When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("679", "Honedge", "Apparently this Pokémon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("680", "Doublade", "When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("681", "Aegislash-shield", "Generations of kings were attended by these Pokémon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("682", "Spritzee", "It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("683", "Aromatisse", "It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("684", "Swirlix", "To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("685", "Slurpuff", "It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("686", "Inkay", "Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("687", "Malamar", "It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any Pokémon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("688", "Binacle", "Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("689", "Barbaracle", "When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("690", "Skrelp", "Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("691", "Dragalge", "Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("692", "Clauncher", "They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("693", "Clawitzer", "Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("694", "Helioptile", "They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("695", "Heliolisk", "They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("696", "Tyrunt", "This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn’t like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("697", "Tyrantrum", "Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("698", "Amaura", "This ancient Pokémon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("699", "Aurorus", "The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("700", "Sylveon", "It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("701", "Hawlucha", "Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("702", "Dedenne", "Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("703", "Carbink", "Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("704", "Goomy", "The weakest Dragon-type Pokémon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesn’t dry out.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("705", "Sliggoo", "It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it can’t see anything.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("706", "Goodra", "This very friendly Dragon-type Pokémon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("707", "Klefki", "These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("708", "Phantump", "These Pokémon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("709", "Trevenant", "It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("710", "Pumpkaboo-average", "The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("711", "Gourgeist-average", "Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("712", "Bergmite", "It blocks opponents’ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("713", "Avalugg", "Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("714", "Noibat", "They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("715", "Noivern", "They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("716", "Xerneas", "Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("717", "Yveltal", "When this legendary Pokémon’s wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("718", "Zygarde", "When the Kalos region’s ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("719", "Diancie", "A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("720", "Hoopa", "This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("721", "Volcanion", "It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. It’s said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("722", "Rowlet", "Silently it glides, drawing near its targets. Before they even notice it, it begins to pelt them with vicious kicks.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("723", "Dartrix", "It throws sharp feathers called blade quills at enemies or prey. It seldom misses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("724", "Decidueye", "Although basically cool and cautious, when it’s caught by surprise, it’s seized by panic.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("725", "Litten", "It doesn’t allow its emotions to be easily seen. Earning its trust takes time. It prefers solitude.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("726", "Torracat", "It boasts powerful front legs. With a single punch, it can bend an iron bar right over.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("727", "Incineroar", "After hurling ferocious punches and flinging furious kicks, it finishes opponents off by spewing fire from around its navel.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("728", "Popplio", "This Pokémon can control water bubbles. It practices diligently so it can learn to make big bubbles.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("729", "Brionne", "It cares deeply for its companions. When its Trainer is feeling down, it performs a cheery dance to try and help.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("730", "Primarina", "Its singing voice is its chief weapon in battle. This Pokémon’s Trainer must prioritize the daily maintenance of its throat at all costs.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("731", "Pikipek", "This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("732", "Trumbeak", "By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of calls and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("733", "Toucannon", "Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("734", "Yungoos", "It wanders around in a never-ending search for food. At dusk, it collapses from exhaustion and falls asleep on the spot.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("735", "Gumshoos", "It adores having Rattata and Raticate for dinner, but as it’s diurnal, it never encounters them. This Pokémon boasts incredible patience.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("736", "Grubbin", "They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("737", "Charjabug", "From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("738", "Vikavolt", "It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with shocking beams of electrical energy.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("739", "Crabrawler", "It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("740", "Crabominable", "It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("741", "Oricorio-baile", "This Oricorio has sipped red nectar. Its passionate dance moves cause its enemies to combust in both body and mind.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("742", "Cutiefly", "Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of people who have auras resembling those of flowers.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("743", "Ribombee", "Some of Ribombee’s pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("744", "Rockruff", "This Pokémon has lived with people since times long ago. It can sense when its Trainer is in the dumps and will stick close by its Trainer’s side.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("745", "Lycanroc-midday", "When properly raised from a young age, it will become a trustworthy partner that will absolutely never betray its Trainer.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("746", "Wishiwashi-solo", "It’s awfully weak and notably tasty, so everyone is always out to get it. As it happens, anyone trying to bully it receives a painful lesson.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("747", "Mareanie", "It’s found crawling on beaches and seafloors. The coral that grows on Corsola’s head is as good as a five-star banquet to this Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("748", "Toxapex", "Those attacked by Toxapex’s poison will suffer intense pain for three days and three nights. Post-recovery, there will be some aftereffects.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("749", "Mudbray", "It has a stubborn, individualistic disposition. Eating dirt, making mud, and playing in the mire all form part of its daily routine.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("750", "Mudsdale", "Its heavy, mud-covered kicks are its best means of attack, and it can reduce large trucks to scrap without breaking a sweat.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("751", "Dewpider", "When it comes across enemies or potential prey, this Pokémon smashes its water-bubble-covered head into them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("752", "Araquanid", "Despite what its appearance suggests, it cares for others. If it finds vulnerable, weak Pokémon, it protectively brings them into its water bubble.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("753", "Fomantis", "They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("754", "Lurantis", "It fires beams from its sickle-shaped petals. These beams are powerful enough to cleave through thick metal plates.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("755", "Morelull", "As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("756", "Shiinotic", "It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("757", "Salandit", "Volcanoes or dry, craggy places are its home. It emanates a sweet-smelling poisonous gas that attracts bug Pokémon, then attacks them.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("758", "Salazzle", "Filled with pheromones, its poisonous gas can be diluted to use in the production of luscious perfumes.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("759", "Stufful", "A touch from anyone except a known friend sends it into a surging frenzy. It’s an incredibly dangerous Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("760", "Bewear", "This Pokémon has the habit of hugging its companions. Many Trainers have left this world after their spines were squashed by its hug.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("761", "Bounsweet", "Although it’s too sugary for human consumption, Bounsweet’s sweat can be watered down into a juice with just the right amount of sweetness.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("762", "Steenee", "This Pokémon is always bouncing around energetically. Other Pokémon are attracted by its lively appearance and pleasant aroma.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("763", "Tsareena", "A Pokémon known for the beauty of its well-shaped legs, it sometimes appears as a mascot in advertisements for beauty salons.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("764", "Comfey", "Baths prepared with the flowers from its vine have a relaxing effect, so this Pokémon is a hit with many people.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("765", "Oranguru", "Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("766", "Passimian", "They battle with hard berries for weapons. Their techniques are passed from the boss to the group, generation upon generation.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("767", "Wimpod", "Its habitat varies from beaches to seabeds. A natural scavenger, it will gleefully chow down on anything edible, no matter how rotten.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("768", "Golisopod", "It battles skillfully with its six arms, but spends most of its time peacefully meditating in caves deep beneath the sea.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("769", "Sandygast", "It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("770", "Palossand", "Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("771", "Pyukumuku", "These Pokémon line the beaches. The sticky mucous that covers their bodies can be used to soothe sunburned skin. How convenient!");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("772", "Type-null", "Due to the danger that this synthetic Pokémon may go on a rampage, it wears a control mask to restrain its power.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("773", "Silvally", "Although its name was Type: Null at first, the boy who evolved it into this form gave it the name by which it is now known.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("774", "Minior-red-meteor", "Strong impacts can knock it out of its shell. This Pokémon was born from mutated nanoparticles.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("775", "Komala", "The log it holds was given to it by its parents at birth. It has also been known to cling to the arm of a friendly Trainer.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("776", "Turtonator", "It gushes fire and poisonous gases from its nostrils. Its dung is an explosive substance and can be put to various uses.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("777", "Togedemaru", "The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("778", "Mimikyu-disguised", "A lonely Pokémon, it conceals its terrifying appearance beneath an old rag so it can get closer to people and other Pokémon.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("779", "Bruxish", "It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder’s shell is no match for it.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("780", "Drampa", "This Pokémon is friendly to people and loves children most of all. It comes from deep in the mountains to play with children it likes in town.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("781", "Dhelmise", "The soul of seaweed adrift in the waves became reborn as this Pokémon. It maintains itself with new infusions of seabed detritus and seaweed.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("782", "Jangmo-o", "They live in mountains where no trace of humans can be detected. Jangmo-o grow little by little as they battle one another.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("783", "Hakamo-o", "It sheds and regrows its scales on a continuous basis. The scales become harder and sharper each time they’re regrown.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("784", "Kommo-o", "Its rigid scales function as offense and defense. In the past, its scales were processed and used to make weapons and other commodities.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("785", "Tapu-koko", "It confuses its enemies by flying too quickly for the eye to follow. It has a hair-trigger temper but forgets what made it angry an instant later.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("786", "Tapu-lele", "As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("787", "Tapu-bulu", "The guardian deity of Ula’ula is a lazy Pokémon. It commands plants to immobilize its foes and then deals them a savage blow with its horns.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("788", "Tapu-fini", "The guardian deity of Poni, it can control water. People say it can create pure water that will wash away any uncleanness.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("789", "Cosmog", "In ages past, it was called the child of the stars. It’s said to be a Pokémon from another world, but no specific details are known.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("790", "Cosmoem", "There’s something accumulating around the black core within its hard shell. People think this Pokémon may come from another world.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("791", "Solgaleo", "This Pokémon is said to be a male evolution of Cosmog. At the activation of its third eye, it departs for another world.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("792", "Lunala", "Said to live in another world, this Pokémon devours light, drawing the moonless dark veil of night over the brightness of day.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("793", "Nihilego", "One of the Ultra Beasts. It’s unclear whether or not this Pokémon is sentient, but sometimes it can be observed behaving like a young girl.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("794", "Buzzwole", "A mysterious life-form called an Ultra Beast. Witnesses saw it pulverize a dump truck with a single punch.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("795", "Pheromosa", "One of the Ultra Beasts. It refuses to touch anything, perhaps because it senses some uncleanness in this world.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("796", "Xurkitree", "It appeared from the Ultra Wormhole. It raided a power plant, so people think it energizes itself with electricity.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("797", "Celesteela", "One kind of Ultra Beast. Witnesses have seen it burn down a forest by expelling gas from its two arms.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("798", "Kartana", "One of the Ultra Beast life-forms, it was observed cutting down a gigantic steel tower with one stroke of its blade.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("799", "Guzzlord", "A dangerous Ultra Beast, it appears to be eating constantly, but for some reason its droppings have never been found.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("800", "Necrozma", "Light is apparently the source of its energy. It has an extraordinarily vicious disposition and is constantly firing off laser beams.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("801", "Magearna", "Its mechanized body is merely a vessel. Its true self is its Soul-Heart, an artificial soul.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("802", "Marshadow", "It lurks in the shadows of others, copying their movements and powers. This Pokémon is craven and cowering.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("803", "Poipole", "This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("804", "Naganadel", "It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("805", "Stakataka", "It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("806", "Blacephalon", "It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It’s apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.");
INSERT INTO Pokemon (id_pokemon, nome, descricao) VALUES ("807", "Zeraora", "It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they’ll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.");
